# Privacy Policy for Bible Daily Companion

**Effective Date:** July 4, 2026

## Overview

Bible Daily Companion ("the App") is designed to work entirely offline and respects your privacy. This policy explains what information the App handles and how.

## Information We Collect

**We do not collect, transmit, or store any of your personal information on external servers.** All data you create in the App — including your name, prayer journal entries, notes, bookmarks, highlights, memorization cards, and reading progress — is stored **locally on your device only**, using your device's local storage.

We do not:
- Require account creation or login
- Collect analytics or usage tracking data
- Share any information with third parties
- Serve advertisements
- Access your contacts, location, camera, or microphone

## Notifications

The App may request permission to send you local notifications (such as a daily verse reminder). These notifications are generated and scheduled entirely on your device. No notification data is sent to or received from any external server.

## Data Storage and Deletion

All data associated with the App is stored in a local database on your device. If you uninstall the App, all locally stored data — including your prayers, notes, bookmarks, highlights, and progress — is permanently deleted along with it. We have no ability to access, recover, or restore this data, as it never leaves your device.

## Bible Text

The Bible text included in the App (King James Version) is in the public domain and is bundled with the App for fully offline use.

## Children's Privacy

The App does not knowingly collect any personal information from anyone, including children under 13. Since no data is collected or transmitted, the App does not present the data-collection risks that this type of policy typically addresses.

## Third-Party Services

The App does not integrate with third-party analytics, advertising, or data-sharing services.

## Changes to This Policy

If this policy changes in the future — for example, if a future update introduces optional cloud sync or account features — this page will be updated, and the "Effective Date" above will reflect the most recent revision.

